items.name: FlexDreamHK
items.description:
23.07.28 ver2.0公開

LittleStepMix_AとのcosineA 0.5マージをしたモデルに、Adjust 0,0,0,0,1,1,2 で色味調整を加えたもの。

パッキリとした太い主線が抑えられ、柔らかさのあるイラストが出力できます。

またイラストで用いられる自然光の表現を簡易的に取り入れる為、色調を青みがかった方向に寄せています。

※顔が自分の理想とする形から離れてしまったので、後日に調整してverUP予定です

　FlexDreamHKはNovelAIモデルの入っていない、あるいは入っているリスクを可能な限り低くしたモデルを目指して作成しました。

　モデル名はマージに使用したモデルたちに敬意を表し、主要なモデル名を組み合わせて命名しています。

　マージ元となったモデルはStable DiffusionやWifu Diffusionへの追加学習（ファインチューニング）を行ったもののみで構成されています。
　また、にじジャーニーと普段使いしているモデルから生成した絵から絵柄LoRAを作成・マージしており、いわゆる蒸留系と呼ばれるモデルでもあります。

　マージの過程と使用したLoRAそのもの、またそれを作成した際のデータセットを開示する事で可能な限り透明性を担保しました。知りたい場合はhugging faceのページをご覧ください。

-------

🎀 特徴

  • 得意なこと

    • 太めの主線でパッキリとしたアニメ調のイラスト

    • soloのかわいい女の子が出しやすい

    • 表情の多様性にやや欠ける

    • 背景メインのイラストは苦手

    • 手指含めて細部の破綻が比較的多め

-------

items.name: Hasui Kawase Style
items.description:
Kawase Hasui, also known as Kawase Bunjiro, was a Japanese artist and printmaker known for his exquisite landscape woodblock prints. Born in 1883, he played a significant role in the Shin-hanga ("New Prints") movement during the early 20th century.

Hasui's prints primarily depicted landscapes and scenes of rural and urban Japan. His works captured the beauty of various seasons, including snow scenes, moonlit nights, and serene landscapes. He had a remarkable ability to convey the atmosphere and mood of a place, infusing his prints with a sense of tranquility and contemplation.

One of his most recognizable series is "Twenty Views of Tokyo," which portrayed iconic locations in and around Tokyo, capturing the city's changing landscapes as it modernized during the early 20th century. Hasui's prints in this series combined traditional Japanese aesthetics with a touch of Western influence.

Hasui employed a meticulous and detailed approach to woodblock printing. His prints showcased his skill in capturing the subtleties of light, texture, and perspective. He collaborated with skilled artisans who helped translate his intricate designs into the final woodblock prints.

Hasui's work gained recognition both in Japan and internationally. His prints were exhibited in Japan, Europe, and the United States, introducing audiences to the beauty of Japanese landscapes and the artistry of woodblock printing.

Kawase Hasui's prints continue to be highly sought after by collectors and art enthusiasts. His contributions to the Shin-hanga movement, with his masterful technique and evocative portrayals of Japanese landscapes, have left a lasting impact on the world of printmaking and continue to inspire artists and admirers of Japanese art.

items.name: Journey to the Gods
items.description:
Introducing Journey to the Gods Model: An AI Model for Evocative Spiritual Journey and Deity Encounters

Journey to the Gods Model is an AI model designed to generate evocative images inspired by the theme of spiritual journeys and encounters with deities. Trained on a collection of diverse and captivating images that encompass the realms of digital art and 3D visuals, this model has undergone 20 epochs and 2380 steps to capture the essence and emotional depth associated with embarking on a spiritual odyssey and communing with celestial beings.

The dataset used to train Journey to the Gods Model was carefully curated to include a wide range of evocative and spiritually resonant imagery. It consists of digital art and 3D visuals that portray awe-inspiring landscapes, ethereal realms, and encounters with mythical or divine entities.

items.name: Kay Nielsen Style
items.description:
Kay Nielsen was a Danish illustrator known for his enchanting and imaginative artwork, particularly in the field of children's books. Born in 1886, Nielsen's illustrations were highly influenced by the Art Nouveau and Golden Age of Illustration movements.

Nielsen's illustrations are characterized by their intricate details, delicate lines, and a sense of ethereal beauty. His use of vivid colors and ornate designs brought his illustrations to life, creating a captivating and fantastical world.

One of his most notable works is his illustrations for the fairy tale collection "East of the Sun and West of the Moon." These illustrations showcased Nielsen's mastery in depicting mythical creatures, enchanted landscapes, and intricate patterns, capturing the magical essence of the fairy tales.

Although Nielsen's career experienced a decline after the popularity of children's book illustration shifted towards more simplified styles, his work has experienced a revival in recent years. His illustrations have been reprinted in various editions, and his influence on subsequent generations of illustrators is widely acknowledged.

Kay Nielsen's illustrations continue to captivate audiences with their whimsical and otherworldly quality. His ability to transport readers into the realms of fantasy and his exceptional artistic skill have cemented his place as a celebrated illustrator of the early 20th century.

items.name: Konstantin Korovin Style
items.description:
Konstantin Korovin was a Russian painter of the late 19th and early 20th centuries. Born in 1861, he was one of the prominent figures of the Russian Impressionist movement.

Korovin's artistic style was characterized by his vibrant and colorful depictions of landscapes, cityscapes, and scenes of everyday life. He had a keen eye for capturing the play of light and shadow, as well as the nuances of atmospheric conditions.

One of his notable bodies of work is his series of paintings showcasing the vibrant city life of Moscow and Saint Petersburg. Korovin's use of bold brushwork and vivid colors captured the bustling streets, festive events, and architectural landmarks of these Russian cities.

His paintings also extended to landscapes, where he depicted the beauty of nature in various seasons and settings. Korovin had a talent for capturing the changing moods of the outdoors, whether it be the warm hues of autumn, the delicate blossoms of spring, or the serene snowy landscapes of winter.

Korovin's versatility as a painter extended beyond landscapes and cityscapes. He also ventured into portraiture and stage design, creating theatrical backdrops and costumes for opera and ballet performances.

His contributions to the art world were highly regarded, and he received numerous awards and honors throughout his career. Korovin's works were exhibited in Russia and internationally, and he played a significant role in promoting Russian Impressionism.

Konstantin Korovin's paintings continue to be admired for their lively colors, evocative atmospheres, and his ability to capture the essence of the Russian landscape and urban life. He remains an influential figure in Russian art history and a celebrated artist of the Impressionist movement.

items.description:
Hey, This is my first LoRA. If you'd like to buy me a coffee, I'd very much appreciate it!

When using this LoRA I find it best to set the weight to around 0.7 give or take.

A resolution of 1280 x 768 or 1280 x 1024 is what I tend to use for good results. I just swap them when generating portrait or landscape.

Checkpoint's:

I like to use NeatNess Fluffy Fur Mix (I prefer the Infinity version)

You can also try Swoonify as well, it also yields great results. I've tried both versions and they both work well.

LoRA's:

I also add a little bit of blindbox/大概是盲盒 when generating usually a weight around 0.4 is nice, I find it adds a little bit of a different style to it.

finally add a little bit of extra detail with Add More Details - Detail Enhancer / Tweaker (细节调整) LoRA around 0.4 or 0.5 is nice.

Textual Inversions:

  1. Deep Negative

  2. EasyNegative

  3. badhandv4 - AnimeIllustDiffusion

  4. Bad artist Negative embedding

VAE:

  • Blessed Vae specifically blessed2.vae.pt.

Trigger words:

Kimiko, Kimiko outfit, pink hair, pink eyes, furry, furry female, fangs, two-tone fur, animal ears, fox ears, white fur, face scar, facial mark, gold symbol on forehead

If you want a rear view pose use the (from behind) trigger word.

All images used to train this LoRA were a resolution of 1024 x 1024.

items.name: 【再世】next life-成奎安
items.description:
这是群星再世第二十七期，以后会不定期出去世的群星Lora，以纪念他们。

成奎安，香港演艺圈“四大恶人”之一，他饰演过阴毒无耻的恶棍，凶恶蛮横的打手，欺男霸女的流氓，耿直仗义的跟班，游手好闲的混混，无恶不作的老大…

同时他也是发哥、星爷、华仔合作最多的搭档，几乎所有的香港一线明星大咖都和他有过精彩的对手戏。他虽然是银幕上的恶人，但却是生活中的好人

蓝洁瑛没戏可接，穷困潦倒，流落街头。大傻去她常待的附近饭店告诉老板，以后蓝洁瑛吃饭都不用给钱，记他账上，他来付，吃多少钱都可以。

张家辉被人敲诈勒索，成奎安拖着病躯，天天陪在张家辉身边，靠着以往的“薄面”，保了张家辉一次。

新入行的陈淑兰在片场受欺负，直接认其做“契女”（同干女儿）……

2004年末在片场拍戏时突然吐血，送医后确诊鼻咽癌，为了治病，他耗尽家财，最艰难时还是尹志强资助150万才撑过难关，是在病情稍微好转的时候，成奎安便把钱还给了尹志强，他说“不想欠人情”，但始终没有治愈。

2009年因鼻咽癌去世，享年54岁。

items.name: 只狼 永真/sekiro Emma/hentai Lora
items.description:
大家好，我是鲷，这次给大家带来的是游戏只狼永真小姐姐Lora。

首先要跟大家说的是，这个模型并不算是一个训练的很成功的模型，他的兼容性不好，手脚崩坏的问题也很常有，而且它只能跟我的impasto大模型或者irises 大模型一起搭配使用，跟其他模型的话会蹦的稀里哗啦。V2版本画风我更喜欢一些，但是很难用，崩坏率超级高，如果你是个初学者，那么我不建议你使用它，V1的兼容性更好一些（也好不到哪去），画风的还原度不如V2，它和我以前发布的那种随便抽卡都能sssr的模型是不同的，它需要你tag写的要稍微好一些，如果不知道咋写可以参考我的例图中的tag。

不过的，总体的画风还算是好看的，抽一抽卡还是能出来还不错的图，我还蛮喜欢的，如果你喜欢这种风格的永真，那么你可以尝试一下。

items.name: Blade Runner 2049  light and shadow Style  / 银翼杀手2049光影风格
items.description:
Blade Runner 2049 light and shadow style Lora

This Lora is trained by some art paintings and stills of my favorite movie --- Blade Runner 2049 (See under for further information and how to use)

银翼杀手2049 光影风格 LORA

此lora运用了我最爱的电影 -银翼杀手2049 的美术绘画以及部分剧照训练而成。(使用方法与简介见下文)

Recommended usage :

The training base model is sd1.4, but it also has many unexpected effects on other base models. have a try!

If the image glitch, try to increase the number of sampling steps or use the img2img with tile upscale to optimize.

This Lora can be used alone as a scene generation, but the generated content may be relatively simple,

The best way to use this Lora is to use it with other subjects, or to mix it with other Lora: add this Lora to the subject you want to generate, for example, add this Lora when generating girls, cars, and indoor scenes ;

It can make the original picture have more intense contrast and colorful light and shadow effects, (cyberpunk's iconic contrast between warm and cold light), more atmospheric perspective effects, MORE light effects, and more storytelling screen light and shadow division  …

推荐用法 ：

训练底模是sd1.4, 但搭配其他底模也能有很多意想不到效果，试着尝试搭配不同的底模吧！

如果画面崩坏，试着调高生成步数，或者后续用图生图tile放大去优化回来

此lora可以单独作为场景生成使用，但是生成内容可能会比较单一，

这个lora最好的使用方式是搭配其他主体使用，或者是与其他lora混合：在你想生成的主体物上再额外加上这个lora，譬如说在生成女孩，汽车，室内场景时加上此lora；

它能够使原本的画面拥有 对比度更加强烈和多彩的光影效果，（赛博朋克风标志性的冷暖光对比），更多的大气透视效果，更丰富的光效，更具故事感的画面光影分割......
